observations.recommendation:
We recommended and the Management agreed that the Local Chief Executive (LCE) direct the:

a. Assistant Municipal Treasurer to:

i. Require all the collectors to remit all their collections daily and in case of collectors assigned to the field, at least once a week or as soon as the collections reach P5,000.00 to the Liquidating Officer and prepare the RCD at the close of the business day or on the next working day;
ii. Deposit intact all collections remitted to her by the Liquidating Officer;
iii. Avoid issuing new sets of accountable forms until all collections were remitted in full by the collectors;
iv. Strengthen the internal control in cash management by observing the proper cut-off in the reporting of collections, particularly the preparation of RCD; and
v. Instruct all the collecting officers to ensure completeness and accuracy of the information on the accountable forms and RCDs such as signatures and dates.

b. Municipal Accountant prepare the necessary adjusting entries to correct the errors.

